Sentencas: Anode supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) based on Ni-Fe bimetal and gadolinia-doped ceria (GDC) composite anode were fabricated and evaluated in the intermediate- and low-temperature range.
Titulo: A promising Ni-Fe bimetallic anode for intermediate-temperature SOFC based on Gd-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: Ni0.75Fe0.25-GDC anode substrate and GDC electrolyte bilayer were prepared by the multi-layered aqueous tape casting method.
Titulo: A promising Ni-Fe bimetallic anode for intermediate-temperature SOFC based on Gd-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: The single cell performance was characterized with La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-GDC (LSCF-GDC) composite cathode.
Titulo: A promising Ni-Fe bimetallic anode for intermediate-temperature SOFC based on Gd-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: The maximum power density reached 330, 567, 835 and 1333 mW cm(-2) at 500, 550, 600 and 650 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: A promising Ni-Fe bimetallic anode for intermediate-temperature SOFC based on Gd-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: Good long-term performance stability has been achieved at 600 degrees C for up to 100 h. The improved single cell performance was achieved in the reduced temperature after the long-term stability test.
Titulo: A promising Ni-Fe bimetallic anode for intermediate-temperature SOFC based on Gd-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: The maximum power density registered 185 and 293 mW cm(-2) at 400 and 450 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: A promising Ni-Fe bimetallic anode for intermediate-temperature SOFC based on Gd-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: The impedance spectra fitting results of the test cell revealed that the improved cell performance was attributed to the much lower electrochemical reaction resistance.
Titulo: A promising Ni-Fe bimetallic anode for intermediate-temperature SOFC based on Gd-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: XRD and SEM examination indicated that the outstanding performance of the single cell seemed to arise from the optimized composition and excellent microstructure of Ni0.75Fe0.25-GDC anode, as well as the improved stability of the anode microstructure with prolonged testing time.
Titulo: A promising Ni-Fe bimetallic anode for intermediate-temperature SOFC based on Gd-doped ceria electrolyte
